item.name: Alarms present
item.description: The present number of active alarm conditions.

item.name: Battery current
item.description: The present battery current.

item.name: Battery status
item.description: This function is not fully supported.A value of batteryLow indicates that the battery voltage is low. A value of unknown indicates that the battery is not connecttd. The value of batteryDepleted is not supported.

item.name: Battery temperature
item.description: The ambient temperature at or near the UPS Battery casing.When the battery temperature sensor is not connected, the value is invalid.

item.name: Battery voltage
item.description: The magnitude of the present battery voltage.

item.name: Bypass frequency
item.description: The present bypass frequency.

item.name: Bypass number lines
item.description: The number of bypass lines utilized in this device. This entry indicates the number of rows in the bypass table.

item.name: Estimated charge remaining
item.description: An estimate of the battery charge remaining expressed as a percent of full charge.

item.name: Estimated minutes remaining
item.description: An estimate of the time to battery charge depletion under the present load conditions if the utility power is off and remains off, or if it were to be lost and remain off.

item.name: Agent software version
item.description: The UPS agent software version. This variable may or may not have the same value as upsIdentUPSSoftwareVersion in some implementations.

item.name: Attached devices
item.description: A string identifying the devices attached to the output(s) of the UPS. This object should be set by the administrator.

item.name: Manufacturer
item.description: The name of the UPS manufacturer.

item.name: Model
item.description: The UPS Model designation.

item.name: Name
item.description: A string identifying the UPS. This object should be set by the administrator.

item.name: UPS software version
item.description: The UPS firmware/software version(s). This variable may or may not have the same value as upsIdentAgentSoftwareVersion in some implementations.

item.name: Input line bads
item.description: A count of the number of times the input entered an out-of-tolerance condition as defined by the manufacturer. This count is incremented by one each time the input transitions from zero out-of-tolerance lines to one or more input lines out-of-tolerance.

item.name: Input number lines
item.description: The number of input lines utilized in this device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the input table.

item.name: Output frequency
item.description: The present output frequency.

item.name: Output number lines
item.description: The number of output lines utilized in this device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the output table.

item.name: Output source
item.description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(2) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker.

item.name: Seconds on battery
item.description: If the unit is on battery power, the elapsed time since the UPS last switched to battery power, or the time since the network management subsystem was last restarted, whichever is less. Zero shall be returned if the unit is not on battery power.

item_prototype.name: Input voltage on line $1
item_prototype.description: The magnitude of the present input voltage.

item_prototype.name: Output percent load on line $1
item_prototype.description: The percentage of the UPS power capacity presently being used on this output line, i.e., the greater of the percent load of true power capacity and the percent load of VA.
